			<!--<p>EHRI-DR-19420323-IT_EN</p>
      <p>Report of the Italian Consul General in Prague, Casto Caruso, to the Ministry of Foreign
        Affairs in Rome and the Italian Embassy in Berlin.</p>
      <p>Cable No. 756/179</p>
      <p>R. Consulate General of <placeName
          ref="https://www.geonames.org/3175395/italian-republic.html">Italy</placeName></p>-->
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-DR-19420323-IT.jpg"/>
			<p>Addressed to R. <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-005042">Ministry of Foreign Affairs</orgName>,
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3169070/rome.html">Rome</placeName></p>
			<p>R. Embassy of Italy, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName></p>
			<p>M <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000287">Mussolini</persName></p>
			<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>, <date when="1942-03-23">23th March 1942</date>. XX</p>
			<p>Re: <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-614" type="subject">Concentration of Jews</term>.</p>
			<p>I have the honour to inform that an important decree concerning the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-575"
					type="subject">transfer</term> of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> to
				a location in the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-places-place-iti-64">Protectorate</placeName>
					(<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-places-place-iti-29">Theresienstadt</placeName>) has been
				published in the Collection of Laws and Decrees of the <ref target="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/admindistricts-212"
					>Reichsprotektor</ref>. With this <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-542" type="subject"
					>measure</term> the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">Jewish element</term> will
				be definitively isolated from the remaining <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject"
					>Aryan</term> population.</p>
			<p>Of course, <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-places-place-iti-29">Theresienstadt</placeName> will have to
				be vacated by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">Aryan</term> citizens. The <ref
					target="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/admindistricts-212">Reichsprotektor’s</ref> decree deals with this <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-585" type="subject">problem</term> and rules that no <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">Aryan</term> person transferred elsewhere shall suffer
				any <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-945" type="subject">material</term> loss. All <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">Aryans</term> living in the area chosen for the
					<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-places-place-iti-64">Protectorate’s</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> will have their losses refunded and
				will be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1039" type="subject">transferred</term> elsewhere in an
				appropriate manner. Clearly, despite this measure, those who are to be transferred will have to bear some sacrifices for the benefit
				of all.</p>
			<p>The local <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-341" type="subject">press</term> emphasizes that these
				sacrifices will in any case be largely offset by the huge advantages that cleansing the <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-places-place-iti-64">Protectorate</placeName> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> will provide to the entire <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czech</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">Aryan</term> population.</p>
			<p>I enclose a full translation of the <ref target="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/admindistricts-212">Reichsprotektor’s</ref>
				decree.</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_dr_caruso_casto">Caruso</persName></p>
